IBADAN – The Oyo state governor, Seyi Makinde, on Wednesday, inaugurated a five-man committee  to critically look into crisis rocking the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology (LAUTECH), Ogbomoso and find a lasting solution to its joint ownership tussle. Members of the committee included ASUU chairman, University of Ibadan,  Prof. Ayodeji Omole, Mr. Bolaji Ayorinde, Mr. Oyelowo Oyewo, Chief Jumoke Akinjide and the state Commissioner for Education, Professor Daud Shangodoyin. While inaugurating the committee, Makinde noted that various crisis rocking LAUTECH could only be laid to rest if the joint ownership issue is resolved. He, therefore, charged the committee to present its preliminary reports within four weeks. Makinde maintained that Oyo state would continue to collaborate with Osun State on other platform, but on the sole ownership of LAUTECH, there was no going back. In his remark, Prof.  Omole, chairman of the committee, assured Makinde and people of Oyo State that they would be professional in the task.